      <akn:section eId="sec_16_1034">
        <akn:num>16-1034</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Training program.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_16-1034_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Police force shall incorporate in its educational program for new law enforcement officers training in:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_16-1034_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The training shall stress the importance of enforcing the law against intrafamily offenses. The Police force may:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_16-1034_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>At least 20 hours of basic training in responding to an intrafamily offense shall be required of any new law enforcement officer prior to the law enforcement officerâ€™s permanent appointment.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_16-1034_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Any currently employed law enforcement officer shall be required to participate in an 8-hour course designed to familiarize the law enforcement officer with the dynamics of intrafamily offenses.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
